@startuml SignalReport - Deployment-Diagramm
!pragma layout smetana
skinparam dpi 150
scale max 16384 width
!theme plain
skinparam deploymentFontSize 13
skinparam linetype ortho

node "Client-Gerät" as Client {
  artifact "Web-Browser" as Browser {
    interface "HTML5 + JavaScript + Chart.js"
  }
}

node "Server-System" as Server {
  node "Java Virtual Machine" as JVM {
    artifact "SignalReport.jar" as App {
      interface "Main Application"
    }

    artifact "Javalin Webserver" as Web {
      interface "HTTP/HTTPS Server (Port 4567)"
    }

    artifact "H2 Database (Twin)" as DB {
      interface "Embedded Twin-Database"
    }
  }

  artifact "config.json" as ConfigFile {
    interface "JSON Configuration"
  }

  artifact "data/" as DataDir {
    interface "signalreport.mv.db (Primary)\nsignalreport-shadow.mv.db (Shadow)\nquarantine/ (defekte DBs)"
  }
}

node "Externe Dienste" as External {
  node "DNS-Server" as DNSServers {
    artifact "Google DNS (8.8.8.8)" as Google
    artifact "Cloudflare DNS (1.1.1.1)" as Cloudflare
    artifact "Quad9 DNS (9.9.9.9)" as Quad9
  }

  node "Web-Server" as WebServers {
    artifact "example.com" as Example
    artifact "heise.de" as Heise
  }

  node "API-Dienste" as APIs {
    artifact "ipify.org" as Ipify
  }
}

Browser --> Web : HTTP/HTTPS Requests
Web --> App : REST-API Calls
App --> DB : JDBC Database Access
App --> ConfigFile : Read/Write Configuration
App --> DNSServers : DNS Queries
App --> WebServers : HTTP Requests
App --> APIs : External IP Lookup

note top of Client
  **Client-Gerät**
  • Desktop-PC, Laptop, Tablet, Smartphone
  • Moderne Web-Browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
  • Keine Installation nötig – läuft im Browser
  • Responsive Design für mobile Geräte
end note

note right of Server
  **Server-System**
  • Windows, macOS, Linux, Synology NAS
  • Java 21+ erforderlich
  • Einzelne JAR-Datei (keine Installation)
  • Portable Twin-Datenbank (H2)
  • Konfiguration in config.json
  • Daten in ./data/ Verzeichnis
  • Crash-resistent durch Spiegelung
end note

note bottom of External
  **Externe Dienste**
  • DNS-Server weltweit (Google, Cloudflare, etc.)
  • Web-Server für HTTP-Messungen
  • ipify.org für externe IP-Ermittlung
  • Keine API-Keys oder Registrierung nötig
  • Alle Dienste kostenlos nutzbar
end note

note left of App
  **Deployment-Szenarien**
  1. **Lokal**: Auf eigenem PC/Laptop
  2. **NAS**: Synology DSM als Hintergrund-Dienst
  3. **Server**: Linux-Server mit systemd-Service
  4. **Cloud**: Docker-Container in Cloud-Umgebung

  **Vorteile**:
  • Keine externen Abhängigkeiten
  • Vollständig offline nutzbar (außer DNS/IP-Abfragen)
  • Einfache Migration zwischen Systemen
  • Backup durch Kopieren von config.json + data/
end note
@enduml